@node "Requirements" "Requirements"
@{lindent 4}


@{b}Requirements@{ub}


In order to run AmiFTP you'll need AmigaOS 4.0 or higher, and a running TCP/IP stack.
You also need to have Martin 'Mason' Mertz AISS installed, you can download it from http://www.masonicons.de/.


Preferably you also need the png.iconmodule from OS4Depot.Net, or you have to replace the included icons with your own.
http://os4depot.net/index.php?function=showfile&file=library/misc/png_im.lha


@{b}Installation@{ub}


The easiest way to install AmiFTP is to just unpack the archive and copy it where you want it.
Before you try to connect to a site, make sure that the anonymous password is set correctly, it's in the menu "Settings/Global".

@endnode

@Node "Usage" "Using AmiFTP"
@{lindent 4}

@{b}Using AmiFTP@{ub}


AmiFTP can be started either from the CLI or from Workbench.


@{" Arguments   " Link "Arguments"}           Command line arguments and Tooltypes.

@{" Main Window " Link "MainWindow"}           Main window.


Some notes/hints about controlling AmiFTP: If you want to force AmiFTP to
re-read the remote dir, press enter in the 'Directory'-gadget. AmiFTP will save
the config-file if it has changed when you exit it.

@EndNode

@node "MainWindow" "Main window"
@{lindent 4}

@{b}Main window@{ub}


Most things in this window need no explanation... more documentation will come in the future.

@endnode

@node "TransferWindow" "Transfer window"
@{lindent 4}

@{b}Transfer window@{ub}


Shows the name of the file being transferred at the moment, also shows total
size, CPS and data transferred. AmiFTP will try to get the true size of a link and
use that as the size instead of -1 that's shown in the filelist.

@endnode

@node "ConnectWindow" "Connect window"
@{lindent 4}

@{b}Connect window@{ub}

Shows the status of the connection, the order of the information is:

@{lindent 8}

'Connecting...'

'Sending login...'

'Sending password...'

'Reading directory..'


@{lindent 4}

Currently you can only Abort AmiFTP at the 'Connecting...' phase.

@endnode

@node "Arguments" "CLI arguments and Workbench ToolTypes"
@{lindent 4}

@{b}Arguments@{ub}


The following arguments are available as cli arguments and Workbench
Tooltypes:


FIXEDFONTNAME - This font is used in the main listview. (currently ignored)


FIXEDFONTSIZE - And the size for the above font. (currently ignored)


ICONIFIED     - Start AmiFTP in iconified mode.


PORTNAME      - The name of AmiFTP's ARexx port.


PROPFONTNAME  - This font is used in all gadgets except the main listview. (currently ignored)


PROPFONTSIZE  - And the size for the above font.(currently ignored)


PUBSCREEN     - Name of the public screen AmiFTP should open on.


SETTINGS      - Tells AmiFTP which preference-file to use.


Note that the fontsettings is currently ignored.




@{b}New arguments in OS4 version@{ub}


DOCKY         - Tells AmiFTP to add an icon to AmiDock for easy access when started.


@endnode

@node "Configuration" "Configuring AmiFTP"
@{lindent 4}

@{b}Configuration of AmiFTP@{ub}


At startup AmiFTP searches for a AmiFTP.xml file in the following directories (in this order):


@{lindent 8}

Current directory, PROGDIR: and ENVARC:

@{lindent 4}

If it can't find a preferences file the default name for it will be PROGDIR:AmiFTP.xml.


You can save the preferences with the menu @{"Settings/Save settings" Link "MENUSaveSettings"}.


@{" Global preferences " Link "Globalpreferences"}  The Global preferences window

@{" Sitelist " Link "Sitelist"}            Sitelist window

@endnode

@node "Globalpreferences" "Global preferences"
@{lindent 4}

@{b}Global preferences@{ub}


@{b}General Page@{ub}


· Anonymous password:
@{lindent 8}

Enter your email-address here, this will be sent to the ftp-server when you log in as anonymous user.

@{lindent 4}


· View command:
@{lindent 8}

Enter the command AmiFTP should use when viewing files, %F in the string will expand to the filename and %P will expand to the name
of the public screen AmiFTP lives on. Note that at the moment you have to specify the complete path for the command if you run AmiFTP from Workbench.

@{lindent 4}


· Default local drawer:
@{lindent 8}

For sites which you don't specify a download directory this directory will be used.

@{lindent 4}


· Buffer size:
@{lindent 8}

The buffer used for reading and writing when transfering files.

@{lindent 4}


· Directory cache size:
@{lindent 8}

The number of cached directorys AmiFTP will save in memory.

@{lindent 4}


· Delete viewed files
@{lindent 8}

AmiFTP stores a copy of viewed files in T:, when this oprion is ticked it deletes them on exit.

@{lindent 4}


· Ignore case:
@{lindent 8}

Case sensitivity in the main listview.

@{lindent 4}


· Disable Prefs warning:
@{lindent 8}

When the main prefs, or the site list, has changed you will get a requester on exit telling you haven't saved your prefs.
With this option ticked AmiFTP will save the prefs and site list automatically on exit, without asking you. This includes
AmiNet date and last visited directory.

@{lindent 4}


· Beep after transfer:
@{lindent 8}

Tells AmiFTP to beep when transfers are complete.

@{lindent 4}


@{b}Aminet Page@{ub}


· Hide drawers:
@{lindent 8}

Pattern matching to hide entries when in AmiNet mode.

@{lindent 4}


· Preserve filepath:
@{lindent 8}

Saves the dirstructure used on AmiNet when downloading files.

@{lindent 4}


· Show MOTD-file:
@{lindent 8}

Recieve and show the AmiNet MOTD (Message Of The Day) file.

@{lindent 4}


· Download readme:
@{lindent 8}

Also downloads the readme when downloading from AmiNet.

@{lindent 4}


@{b}Display Page@{ub}


· Open on default public screen:
@{lindent 8}

With this ticked AmiFTP opens on default public screen. This is normally the Workbench screen.

@{lindent 4}


· Public screen:
@{lindent 8}

Only available if "Open on default public screen" is not ticked. The name of the screen AmiFTP should open on.
If it can't find this screen, the default public screen will be used.

@{lindent 4}


· Use system fonts:
@{lindent 8}

Use the fonts the rest of the system uses.

@{lindent 4}


· Interface font:
@{lindent 8}

Font to use for labels, gadgets and such.

@{lindent 4}


· Filelist font:
@{lindent 8}

Font to use for filelist in the main window.

@{lindent 4}


· Show toolbar graphics:
@{lindent 8}

Use Mason's AISS for graphics in the toolbar. If both this one and "Show toolbar text" is not ticked the toolbar won't show.

@{lindent 4}


· Show toolbar text:
@{lindent 8}

Show text in the toolbar buttons. If both this one and "Show toolbar graphics" is not ticked the toolbar won't show.

@{lindent 4}


@{b}Proxy Page@{ub}


@{b}Proxy settings are disabled since AmiFTP was coded with a particular proxy, that is not used elsewhere.@{ub}


· Proxy host:
@{lindent 8}

The name of the proxy-host to use for proxy-connections. Note that
the proxy that AmiFTP needs is not generally available, it will
not work with the Cern httpd-proxy function.

@{lindent 4}


· Proxy port:
@{lindent 8}

Which port on the proxy-host to use.

@{lindent 4}


· Use proxy as default?
@{lindent 8}

Should AmiFTP use the proxy for all connections? You can override this with the proxy-flag for each site.


@{b}Proxy settings are disabled since AmiFTP was coded with a particular proxy, that is not used elsewhere.@{ub}

@{lindent 4}


@{b}Log Page@{ub}


· Show Log:
@{lindent 8}

Turns the new Log listbrowser, at the bottom of the window, on or off. The old log window is now removed.

@{lindent 4}

· Number lines in log:
@{lindent 8}

The number of lines before AmiFTP starts removing the oldest entries in the log.

@{lindent 4}


@endnode

@Node "Sitelist"
@{lindent 4}

@{b}The sitelist window@{ub}


There are two ways to get to this window, and depending on how you got here things look and act different. If you got here via the
"Settings/iSitelist" , double-clicking on a site will pop up the @{"Site configuration window" link "Siteconfiguration"}.
If you got here from the Connect-gadget in the main window, you will have one 'Connect'-gadget and one 'Cancel'-gadget instead of the single 'OK' gadget.
Also double-clicking on a site will make AmiFTP connect to it.

@EndNode

@Node "Siteconfiguration" "Site configuration"
@{lindent 4}


@{b}Site configuration@{ub}


· Name:
@{lindent 8}

This name will show up in the sitelist window and in the hotlist-menu.

@{lindent 4}

· Site:
@{lindent 8}

This should be the ftpsite's actual Internet address (either hostname or IP).

@{lindent 4}

· Port:
@{lindent 8}

Normally all ftp-sites use port-number 21 (which is the default), but some sites are on other ports.

@{lindent 4}

· Auto-cd to directory:
@{lindent 8}

If this is set, AmiFTP will cd to this directory right after the connection is made. It's convenient to have /pub/aminet here for the Aminet sites.

@{lindent 4}

· Save last dir visited:
@{lindent 8}

If this is set, AmiFTP will save the last dir you visited, when disconnecting from a site.

@{lindent 4}

· Download path:
@{lindent 8}

If you click on the button a path-requester will show up, you can also type the download path into the string gadget.
If you don't specify a path, the default path specified in @{"Global preferences" Link "Globalpreferences"} will be used.

@{lindent 4}

· Anonymous login?
@{lindent 8}

Self explaining!

@{lindent 4}

· Login name:
@{lindent 8}

Which loginname to use for non-anonymous logins.

@{lindent 4}

· Password:
@{lindent 8}

The password for the above username. If you don't specify one, AmiFTP will pop up a requester asking for it when you connect. The password will
be saved in the AmiFTP.xml file, and written out in plain ASCII, so if you load the prefs-file into an editor you can read or edit the password.

@{lindent 4}

· Operating System
@{lindent 8}

In order to parse the directory listing correctly, AmiFTP needs to know what Operating System the site is using.
For most sites, UNIX will work. Supported systems are UNIX, VMS and MSDOS. If you connect to a Amiga-site you can try UNIX,
it all depends on which ls the server is using. AmiFTP can't parse the default AmiTCP:bin/ls.

@{lindent 4}

· Proxy:
@{lindent 8}

This is mostly for my personal use since the proxy-support in AmiFTP is not compataible with the www-proxys that are available. This proxy is
only used locally at rydnet.lysator.liu.se.

@{lindent 4}

· Hotlist:
@{lindent 8}

If this is checked the site will appear under the menu-label "HotList".

@{lindent 4}

@EndNode

