@node "MENUReconnect"
@toc "AmiFTPMenus"
@{lindent 4}

@{b}Reconnect@{ub}


Reconnects you to the last server you were connected to this session, and goes to the directory you were in.

@endnode

@node "MENUAddToSiteList"
@toc "AmiFTPMenus"
@{lindent 4}

@{b}Add to sitelist@{ub}


Add the current site to the sitelist, the current remote directory will also be copied.

@endnode

@node "MENUIconify"
@toc "AmiFTPMenus"
@{lindent 4}

@{b}Iconify@{ub}


Removes the gui-interface and puts an icon on the workbench so you can re-open the gui again.

@endnode

@node "MENUAbout"
@toc "AmiFTPMenus"
@{lindent 4}

@{b}About@{ub}


Pops up the About-window.

@endnode

@node "MENUQuit"
@toc "AmiFTPMenus"
@{lindent 4}

@{b}Quit@{ub}


Exits AmiFTP. If configuration has changed since starting AmiFTP a requester will pop up asking if you want to save or not.

@endnode

@node "MENUTagAll"
@toc "AmiFTPMenus"
@{lindent 4}

@{b}Tag all@{ub}


Selects all files in the current remote directory.

@endnode

@node "MENUUntagAll"
@toc "AmiFTPMenus"
@{lindent 4}

@{b}Untag all@{ub}


Deselects all selected files.

@endnode

@node "MENUTransferMode"
@toc "AmiFTPMenus"
@{lindent 4}

@{b}Transfer mode@{ub}


You can switch between binary mode and ASCII-mode.

@endnode

@node "MENUClearCache"
@toc "AmiFTPMenus"
@{lindent 4}

@{b}Clear cache@{ub}


Clears the directory cache.

@endnode

@node "MENUDelete"
@toc "AmiFTPMenus"
@{lindent 4}

@{b}Delete@{ub}


Deletes the selected files. Be careful! You have been warned.

@endnode

@node "MENUSort"
@toc "AmiFTPMenus"
@{lindent 4}

@{b}Sort@{ub}


The will sort the filelist either by Name or Date.

@endnode

@node "MENUGlobal"
@toc "AmiFTPMenus"
@{lindent 4}

@{b}Global settings@{ub}


Opens the @{"Global settings window" link "Globalpreferences"}.

@endnode

@node "MENUSitelist"
@toc "AmiFTPMenus"
@{lindent 4}

@{b}Hostlist@{ub}


Opens the @{"Sitelist window" link "Sitelist"}.

@endnode

@node "MENUImportOldSettings"
@toc "AmiFTPMenus"
@{lindent 4}

@{b}Import old settings@{ub}


Import settings from the old IFF format. You will have to use the menu item @{"Save settings" link "MENUSaveSettings"} and restart AmiFTP
to fully use your old settings.

@endnode

@node "MENULoadSettings"
@toc "AmiFTPMenus"
@{lindent 4}

@{b}Load settings@{ub}


Load new settings.

@endnode

@node "MENUSaveSettings"
@toc "AmiFTPMenus"
@{lindent 4}

@{b}Save settings@{ub}


Save the current settings to file. When starting AmiFTP it looks for AmiFTP.xml in 'Current directory', PROGDIR:, ENVARC: and ~home/.
AmiFTP will also save the current size and position of the main window to the config-file.

@endnode

@node "MENUSaveSettingsAs"
@toc "AmiFTPMenus"
@{lindent 4}

@{b}Save settings as@{ub}


Save the current settings to file specified by the user. An ASL requester pops up to select destination and name.
This file can later be loaded into AmiFTP either chosing @{"Load settings..." link "MENULoadSettings"} from the Settings menu,
or by using the SETTINGS @{"tooltype" Link "Arguments"}.

@endnode

@node "MENUHotList"
@toc "AmiFTPMenus"
@{lindent 4}

@{b}Hotlist@{ub}


If you have checked the 'Hotlist'-gadget in @{"Site configuration" link "Siteconfiguration"} for one or more sites,
this menu will provide an easy way to connect to your favourite site without going through the @{"Sitelist window" link "Sitelist"}.

@endnode

@node "ARexx" "ARexx documenation"
@prev "AmiFTPMenus"
@next "Acknowledgements"
@{lindent 4}

@{b}ARexx@{ub}


AmiFTP's ARexx-port default name is "AMIFTP". In case a command fails a non-zero returncode is returned.

The following ARexx commands are available:


@{" GETATTR " Link "GETATTR"} 

@{" SETATTR " Link "SETATTR"} 

@{" CONNECT " Link "CONNECT"} 

@{" DISCONNECT " Link "DISCONNECT"} 

@{" CD " Link "CD"} 

@{" LCD " Link "LCD"} 

@{" DELETE " Link "DELETE"}

@{" SITE " Link "SITE"} 

@{" GET " Link "GET"} 

@{" MGET " Link "MGET"} 

@{" PUT " Link "PUT"} 

@{" MPUT " Link "MPUT"} 

@{" QUIT " Link "QUIT"} 

@EndNode

@Node "GETATTR" "GETATTR"
@Toc "ARexx"
@{lindent 4}

@{b}GETATTR@{ub}


Syntax: GETATTR STEM/A, HOTLIST/S, FILELIST/S


Description:


Fills the STEM-variable with current AmiFTP-status:

@{lindent 8}

stem.VERSION   = Version of AmiFTP

stem.SCREEN    = Name of the public screen AmiFTP lives on

stem.HOST      = Current host

stem.PORT      = Current port

stem.PROXYHOST = Name of proxyhost

stem.PROXYPORT = Proxyport

stem.USEPROXY  = Use proxy for this connection?

stem.ANONYMOUS = Set to 1 if anonymous login is used, otherwise 0

stem.USERNAME  = Loginname used

stem.LOCALDIR  = Current localdirectory

stem.REMOTEDIR = Current remotedirectory

stem.CONNECTED = Set to 1 if AmiFTP is connected, otherwise 0. (AmiFTP will send a "NOOP"-command in order to check this)

@{lindent 4}

If HOSTLIST is specified the following structure will also be set:

@{lindent 8}

stem.HOTLIST.COUNT       = Number of hotlist entries

stem.HOTLIST.n.NAME      = Host hotlist name

stem.HOTLIST.n.ADDRESS   = Host address

stem.HOTLIST.n.PORT      = Port number to use

stem.HOTLIST.n.USERNAME  = Loginname

stem.HOTLIST.n.ANONYMOUS = Set to 1 if anonymous login should be used

stem.HOTLIST.n.REMOTEDIR = Default remote directory

stem.HOTLIST.n.LOCALDIR  = Default local directory

stem.HOTLIST.n.USEPROXY  = Set to 1 if proxy should be used

@{lindent 4}

If FILELIST is specified AmiFTP will also fill the stem with the current remote directory listing (if there is one available)

@{lindent 8}

stem.FILELIST.COUNT      = Number of files

stem.FILELIST.n.NAME     = Filename

stem.FILELIST.n.SIZE     = Filesize

stem.FILELIST.n.TYPE     = 'FILE' for regular file, 'DIR' for directory and 'LINK' if AmiFTP can't figure out what it is.

@EndNode

@Node "SETATTR" "SETATTR"
@Toc "ARexx"
@{lindent 4}

@{b}SETATTR@{ub}


Syntax: SETATTR HOST/K, PORT/K, USEPROXY/S, REMOTEDIR/K, LOCALDIR/K, USERNAME/K, PASSWORD/K


Description:
@{lindent 8}

Sets the attribute to specified value.

@{lindent 4}

@EndNode

@Node "CONNECT" "CONNECT"
@Toc "ARexx"
@{lindent 4}

@{b}CONNECT@{ub}


Syntax: CONNECT NOSCAN/S


Description:
@{lindent 8}

Connects AmiFTP to a server, you must have specified which server you want to connect to with either 'SETATTR HOST server' or 'SITE
servername'. If you don't want AmiFTP to read the remote directory use the NOSCAN option.

@{lindent 4}

@EndNode

@Node "DISCONNECT" "DISCONNECT"
@Toc "ARexx"
@{lindent 4}

@{b}DISCONNECT@{ub}


Syntax: DISCONNECT


Description:
@{lindent 8}

Disconnect AmiFTP from the current server. It is safe to call DISCONNECT even if you're not connected to a server.

@{lindent 4}

@EndNode

@Node "CD" "CD"
@Toc "ARexx"
@{lindent 4}

@{b}CD@{ub}


Syntax: CD NOSCAN/S, PARENT/S, DIR


Description:
@{lindent 8}

Changes remote directory to DIR or PARENT. If you don't want AmiFTP to read the directory use the NOSCAN option.

@{lindent 4}

@EndNode

@Node "LCD" "LCD"
@Toc "ARexx"
@{lindent 4}

@{b}LCD@{ub}


Syntax: LCD DIR


Description:
@{lindent 8}

Changes local directory to DIR.

@{lindent 4}

@EndNode

@Node "DELETE" "DELETE"
@Toc "ARexx"
@{lindent 4}

@{b}DELETE@{ub}


Syntax: DELETE FILE/M


Description:
@{lindent 8}

Deletes all files, if something goes wrong, AmiFTP will not continue to delete the rest of the files in the list.

@{lindent 4}

@EndNode

@Node "SITE" "SITE"
@Toc "ARexx"
@{lindent 4}

@{b}SITE@{ub}


Syntax: SITE SITE/A/F


Description:
@{lindent 8}

Scans the sitelist and, if the SITE is present, makes AmiFTP ready to connect to the site. Use the CONNECT-command to connect.

@{lindent 4}

@EndNode

@Node "GET" "GET"
@Toc "ARexx"
@{lindent 4}

@{b}GET@{ub}


Syntax: GET ASCII/S, BIN/S, FILE/A, LOCAL


Description:
@{lindent 8}

Gets a file from server in ASCII or BINary mode (default is binary), with the filename LOCAL if specified, otherwise the filename will be the same as FILE.

@{lindent 4}

@EndNode

@Node "MGET" "MGET"
@Toc "ARexx"
@{lindent 4}

@{b}MGET@{ub}


Syntax: MGET ASCII/S, BIN/S, FILE/M


Description:
@{lindent 8}

Gets multiple files in ASCII or BINary mode (default is binary) from the server.

@{lindent 4}

@EndNode

@Node "PUT" "PUT"
@Toc "ARexx"
@{lindent 4}

@{b}PUT@{ub}


Syntax: PUT FILE, REMOTE


Description:
@{lindent 8}

Uploads FILE to the server.

@{lindent 4}

@EndNode

@Node "MPUT" "MPUT"
@Toc "ARexx"
@{lindent 4}

@{b}MPUT@{ub}


Syntax: MPUT FILE/M


Description:
@{lindent 8}

Uploads multiple files to the server.

@{lindent 4}

@EndNode

@Node "QUIT" "QUIT"
@Toc "ARexx"
@{lindent 4}

@{b}QUIT@{ub}


Syntax: QUIT


Description:
@{lindent 8}

Quits AmiFTP, if you are connected to a server AmiFTP will disconnect you first.

@{lindent 4}

@endnode

@node "FAQ"
@prev "ARexx"
@{lindent 4}

@{b}Common questions@{ub}


Why doesn't the proxy-function work for me?


Simple, it's not designed to work with anything else than a local ftp-proxy we use here at rydnet.lysator.liu.se. 
It's in no way compatible with the common http/ftp-proxies available.

@endnode

@node "Acknowledgements"
@prev "FAQ"
@{lindent 4}

@{b}Acknowledgements@{ub}


After a tip from Vicente Gimeno, Guru Meditation sought out Magnus Lilja and talked to him about his AmiFTP program.
Shortly thereafter, Mr Lilja dug up his old Amiga from the closet and managed to find the old sources.
These were sent to us in order to continue the work on this great program.
Joachim Birging has been busy reworking the code to be OS 4 compliant and now is the time to let you all try it out.



